# Wild Spider product spec

The authoritative product specification lives at **[docs/WILD_SPIDER_SPEC.md](docs/WILD_SPIDER_SPEC.md)**.

Before implementing or changing any of the following, **read or re-read that doc** and treat it as the source of truth (unless the user explicitly overrides it in chat):

- Game setup: tableau, stock, jokers, columns, deals, seeds, scoring, undo
- Card moves, foundation, dealing from stock, empty-column rules
- Powers (joker/set), achievements, deck pairs, UI views and popups described there
- Animation/sound behaviour tied to those rules

If code and the spec disagree, **flag the mismatch to the user** instead of silently guessing.

When you change behaviour that the spec describes, **update `docs/WILD_SPIDER_SPEC.md` in the same change** so the doc stays accurate.
